Input: On receipt of the Stop signal, the software turns OFF the Heater, turns OFF the Cooking Lamp, and enters a wait state.
Expected Output :
Identified data groups = {
  "Stop button": {
    "Stop signal": {
      "Attributes": ["Stop signal"]
    }
  },
  "Heater": {
    "Heater On/Off command": {
      "Attributes": ["Turn OFF command"]
    }
  },
  "Cooking lamp": {
    "Cooking lamp On/Off command": {
      "Attributes": ["Turn OFF command"]
    }
  }
}

Input: On receipt of a 30-second signal the software receives the 30-second signal, waits for and receives the elapsed time signal, retrieves the current cooking mode from the RAM, gets a new target temperature for this cooking mode by obtaining it from the relationship stored in the ROM and stores this new target temperature into the RAM.
Expected Output :
Identified data groups = {
  "Timer": {
    "30-second signal": {
      "Attributes": ["30-second signal"]
    },
    "Current elapsed time signal": {
      "Attributes": ["Current elapsed time"]
    }
  },
  "Current settings": {
    "Current cooking mode": {
      "Attributes": ["Current cooking mode"]
    },
    "Current target temperature": {
      "Attributes": ["Current target temperature"]
    }
  },
  "Target settings": {
    "New target temperature": {
      "Attributes": ["New target temperature", "Cooking mode", "Elapsed time"]
    }
  }
}

Input: On receipt of the Start signal, the software sends Turn ON signals to both the Cooking Lamp and the Heater.
Expected Output :
Identified data groups = {
  "Start button": {
    "Start signal": {
      "Attributes": ["Start signal"]
    }
  },
  "Cooking lamp": {
    "Cooking lamp On/Off command": {
      "Attributes": ["Turn ON command"]
    }
  },
  "Heater": {
    "Heater On/Off command": {
      "Attributes": ["Turn ON command"]
    }
  }
}

Input: When a Registrar wishes to enter data about a new Professor, he selects the sub-option 'Add Professor' and enters Professor details including ID, name, address, social security number, Department, qualifications and contact details.
Expected Output :
Identified data groups = {
  "Professor": {
    "Professor details": {
      "Attributes": ["Professor ID", "Name", "Address", "Social Security Number", "Department", "Qualifications", "Contact details"]
    }
  },
  "Errors": {
    "Error Messages": {
      "Attributes": ["Error message", "Validation message"]
    }
  }
}
